== Sriracha Mayo ==

Put the @mayonnaise{1} with the @water{1/2} and half the @sriracha sauce{} in a #small bowl{}.

> See ingredient list for amount of water.

== Sticky Sesame Sauce ==

Put the @ginger puree{1} in a #small saucepan{}, along with the @honey{30}, @soy sauce{12.5}, remaining @sriracha sauce{}, half the @sesame oil{24} and half the @sesame seeds{15}. Put on medium heat, bubble away until sticky and thick, ~{3-4%mins}, reduce the heat if necessary. Stir every minute.

== Cucumber Pickle ==

Meanwhile, trim the @cucumber{3/4} and thinly slice. Put the @rice wine vinegar{15} and remaining sesame oil in a #bowl{} with a pinch of @salt{}, @sugar{} and @pepper{}, mix, add the cucumber, toss to combine.

> About 20cm/8" cucumber works well for this amount.

== Sweet Potato Chips ==

Preheat the #oven{} to 210°C. Pop the @sweet potato fries{250} onto a #baking tray{}, drizzle with a little @oil{}, and season with a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}. Arrange them in a single layer and put them onto the top shelf of the oven to cook until golden, ~{18-20%mins}. Turn halfway through. Halve the @burger buns{2} and add them to the oven for the last ~{5%mins} of cooking time.

== Halloumi ==

Meanwhile, slice the @halloumi{125} - 2 slices per person. Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. Once hot, add the halloumi and fry until golden, ~{2-3%mins} each side. Remove the halloumi from the pan to a #plate{}, cover with #foil{} and leave to the side.

== Chicken ==

Put your pan back on medium-high heat and add enough @oil{} to coat the bottom of the pan. This will ensure the chicken gets really crisp. Once the oil is hot, lay in the @British chicken thighs{2}, flatten them down, fry until crispy and golden, ~{12-14%mins}. Turn every ~{2-3%mins}. Discard any @cornflour{20} left in the bowl.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands after handling raw meat.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Once cooked, remove from the heat, place the chicken on #kitchen paper{}.

== Assembly ==

Lay a chicken thigh on the bottom half of each bun. Spoon the sticky sesame sauce over the top of the chicken thighs, followed by a few slices of cucumber and the halloumi. Top with a small spoonful of sriracha mayo and the burger top. Serve the sweet potato chips on the side and drizzle over the remaining sriracha mayo. Sprinkle over the remaining sesame seeds and then serve the remaining cucumber pickle on the side. Enjoy!